The paper deals with the problem of influence maximization in diffusion networks, which is a topic that falls under the broad area of social network analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of Markov chains, which is a common tool in the study of stochastic processes, and hence cs.SD (Systems and Control) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also deals with optimization problems, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper involves experiments on synthetic and real-world networks, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Humans).
